    "faq": {
      "faqTitle": "Frequently Asked Questions (FAQ)",
      "question": "Question",
      "answer": "Answer",
      "q1": "What is Vitograph's main superpower?",
      "a1": "Vitograph is not just a calorie tracker or a test folder. It is a unified AI-brain that 'sees' the whole picture. The app links what you eat (Diary) with how you feel (Symptoms), and what is happening inside your body (Tests). Based on these data, the Assistant builds a personalized health strategy.",
      "q2": "How is the 'Diary' tab different from the 'Assistant'?",
      "a2": "<p>The Diary is your smart food calculator. You should write (or send photos) of what you ate there. For example: '3-egg omelet with bacon and coffee.' AI recognizes the dish, calculates the glycemic response and micronutrients (vitamins, minerals).</p><p>The Assistant (Aibolit) is your personal health coach. You can consult, discuss your tests, ask to create a daily menu, or complain about ringing in your ears. He remembers your context and profile.</p>",
      "q3": "I uploaded my tests, but the norms differ from the ones on the Invitro/Gemotest form. Why?",
      "a3": "Laboratory reference values show the 'average temperature in the hospital' – the norm for people of all ages and conditions from 18 to 99 years. Vitograph uses dynamic personalized norms (optimums). They are calculated individually for your age, gender, current diseases, and goals. Therefore, a value considered 'normal' by the laboratory may be highlighted in yellow as requiring attention.",
      "q4": "How does test uploading work?",
      "a4": "You can drag a PDF file or upload a bunch of photos of your forms (up to 10 at a time). Important: The AI needs time to carefully 'read' each photo. This process can take from 30 seconds to 2 minutes. You will see a progress bar: just wait for the analysis to complete, and the results will turn into interactive cards. You can always manually correct the number if the AI made a mistake.",
      "q5": "Why are photos of nails, skin, and tongue needed in the Tests tab?",
      "a5": "This is somatic diagnostics. Our body often gives visual signals about vitamin deficiencies or digestive problems even before they are reflected in blood biochemistry. AI is trained to recognize patterns (e.g., white spots on nails or coating on the tongue) and correlate them with specific nutrient deficiencies.",
      "q6": "Does Vitograph replace going to the doctor?",
      "a6": "No. Vitograph is a powerful analytical tool and your personal health navigator, but it does not diagnose medical conditions or prescribe treatments. All insights and AI recommendations are created for you to discuss them substantively with your doctor.",
      "q7": "Are my data confidential?",
      "a7": "Yes. Your medical data, tests, and questionnaires are stored in a secure database. The AI uses them exclusively for personalizing recommendations within your protected sessions.",
      "q8": "How do goals work and how can I create them?",
      "a8": "Goals are created through a simple chat request (e.g., 'I want to lose 5 kg'). It's important to understand: Vitograph doesn't just give you a static schedule. A unique virtual AI specialist is created for your specific goal. This agent takes responsibility for your progress: they will track execution daily, analyze your data, and proactively adjust the plan to ensure you reach the result."
    },
    "about": {
      "title": "About the App",
      "intro1": "Modern medicine is used to treating symptoms when the mechanism is already broken. We at Vitograph believe in a different approach:",
      "intro2": "health starts at the cellular level, long before diseases appear.",
      "description": "Vitograph is your intelligent digital health architect. We have created a platform that combines advanced AI technologies with the principles of evidence-based medicine, nutrition, and biohacking.",
      "howTitle": "How do we do it?",
      "pillar1Title": "Assembling the puzzle.",
      "pillar1Desc": "Your blood tests, sleep quality, stress level, and every eaten plate of food are no longer separate data. Vitograph analyzes them comprehensively 24/7.",
      "pillar2Title": "Seeking the optimum, not the 'norm'.",
      "pillar2Desc": "We do not rely on average laboratory references. We calculate your ideal indicators (dynamic norms), considering your age, profile, and genetic characteristics.",
      "pillar3Title": "Acting proactively.",
      "pillar3Desc": "The AI Assistant notices hidden deficiencies and correlations in your food diary even before they become a problem, helping to correct the condition with precise changes in food and supplements.",
      "closing": "We do not replace doctors. We provide you with a tool to understand your body, feed your cells what they really need, and find your ideal balance. Start with your profile – and let science and data work for your longevity."
    },
